2) Constitutional Language Protocol (CLP) Alignment

Use of this Software within systems that follow the Constitutional Language Protocol (CLP) is explicitly permitted and encouraged.

CLP-compliant implementations may integrate this Software without royalty, provided they do not commercialize the governance layer itself.

3) Commercial Use Requires Separate Agreement

Commercial Use of the Software, where the Software is materially incorporated into a commercial product, governance framework, or derivative automation system, requires a separate written agreement (“Commercial Addendum”) with the Licensor.

Under such Commercial Addendum, the Licensor may receive up to five percent (5%) ownership interest in derivative intellectual property directly created from substantial incorporation of the Software.

For clarity:

“Derivative intellectual property” means newly created software modules, governance frameworks, or automation architectures materially built from or embedding the Software.

Derivative intellectual property does NOT include:
- Data produced by the Software
- End-user business logic
- Manufacturing outputs
- PLC or control logic not derived from the Software itself
- Independent systems that merely interface with the Software

Absent a Commercial Addendum, Commercial Use is not granted under this License.

